Implements Task 1 of TODO.md, part of s-5flv.

Add two public methods to `src/diagram-viewer.js`:

1. `loadFromUrl(url)`:
   - Resolve `url` against `document.baseURI` (so a relative path works);
   - Clear `localStorage[storageKey]` for this instance;
   - Derive a new `base-path` by stripping the trailing path segment from the resolved URL (URLs ending with `/` keep the full path; fully-qualified `https://…` URLs are honoured);
   - Update `base-path` and `manifest` attributes for reflection;
   - Fetch the URL, parse JSON, call `loadData(data)`;
   - On fetch/parse error, surface the existing `#showManifestError` UI.

2. `openJsonDialog()`: extract the body of the existing internal `json-open` listener so it can be called by both the loader and any internal trigger.

Then refactor the existing internal `json-open` listener to call `openJsonDialog()` so behaviour is preserved. Keep `reset()` unchanged — the loader will call it directly.

This is the foundation child; it has no incoming blockers.

Implements R2 of s-79ur (TODO.md task 2).

In each component module, replace the per-instance `#sheet = new CSSStyleSheet()` field (or the existing `static #styles` in diagram-viewer.js) with story-mapper's module-scoped lazy pattern:

```js
let _sharedSheet = null;
function getSharedSheet() {
  if (!_sharedSheet && styles) {
    _sharedSheet = new CSSStyleSheet();
    _sharedSheet.replaceSync(styles);
  }
  return _sharedSheet;
}
```

Then in each constructor (after `attachShadow`):
```js
this.shadowRoot.adoptedStyleSheets = [getSharedSheet()];
```

Apply to all five components: diagram-canvas, diagram-help-modal, diagram-loader, diagram-nav-tree, diagram-viewer. Convert diagram-viewer's existing `static #styles` to the module-scoped lazy form for consistency.

If any component mutates its sheet at runtime, keep a per-instance sheet there and add a code comment explaining why.

Provide implementation feedback on s-79ur covering: per-component before/after, any sheets that had to stay per-instance and why.
